# niri

## Arch packages

```
pacman -S niri pipewire pipewire-alsa pipewire-pulse wireplumber xdg-desktop-portal-gtk gnome-keyring swaybg swayidle swaylock fuzzel cliphist wl-clipboard brightnessctl waybar mako
```

| Package | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| pipewire | audio/video |
| pipewire-alsa | ALSA compatibility |
| pipewire-pulse | PulseAudio compatibility |
| wireplumber | session manager for pipewire |
| xdg-desktop-portal-gtk | default fallback portal (file pickers, etc.) |
| gnome-keyring | Secret portal (password storage) |
| niri | scrollable-tiling Wayland compositor |
| swaybg | wallpaper |
| swayidle | idle timeout (screen off, lock) |
| swaylock | screen locker |
| fuzzel | app launcher + clipboard menu |
| cliphist | clipboard history storage |
| wl-clipboard | wl-paste/wl-copy (clipboard integration) |
| brightnessctl | backlight control |
| waybar | status bar |
| mako | notifications |

## Post-install

Start the pipewire services (only needed once):

```
systemctl --user start pipewire wireplumber pipewire-pulse
```

## systemd user services

Symlinked from this directory into `~/.config/systemd/user/` by the install script:

- `swaybg.service` — wallpaper
- `swayidle.service` — idle management (lock + screen off)
- `wl-clipboard.service` — clipboard watcher (`wl-paste --watch cliphist store`)

Wired into niri with:

```
systemctl --user add-wants niri.service swaybg.service
systemctl --user add-wants niri.service swayidle.service
systemctl --user add-wants niri.service wl-clipboard.service
```
